1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,266
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,266 --> 00:00:02,500
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,849 --> 00:00:05,008
One, two, three.

4
00:00:09,685 --> 00:00:11,611
Three, four, one, two.

5
00:00:12,909 --> 00:00:13,909
To the side.

6
00:00:16,798 --> 00:00:18,595
Three, four, one, two.

7
00:00:27,627 --> 00:00:29,008
What on earth is going on?

8
00:00:29,940 --> 00:00:30,940
Hey!

9
00:00:31,464 --> 00:00:33,840
What? Hey!

10
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:36,283
That darn woman!

11
00:00:37,213 --> 00:00:38,493
What is wrong with you?

12
00:00:40,015 --> 00:00:43,029
You're dead meat today!

13
00:00:43,953 --> 00:00:45,719
Stop it, ma'am!

14
00:00:50,957 --> 00:00:52,952
She pulled out all my hair!

15
00:00:53,825 --> 00:00:56,309
We'll end today's class here.

16
00:00:56,390 --> 00:00:57,990
- Good work.
- Thank you.

17
00:00:58,118 --> 00:00:59,118
What?

18
00:01:00,915 --> 00:01:02,501
What in the world happened?

19
00:01:03,118 --> 00:01:04,152
Are you okay, Yeon Ja?

20
00:01:04,896 --> 00:01:06,648
Yes...

21
00:01:06,893 --> 00:01:09,043
I'm so dumbfounded,
I don't even know what to say.

22
00:01:09,043 --> 00:01:12,139
What grudge does she have against me?
Seriously!

23
00:01:12,488 --> 00:01:15,320
The whole time we were dancing,

24
00:01:15,320 --> 00:01:18,160
she kept going after your hair.

25
00:01:18,379 --> 00:01:19,944
Why did you stop me?

26
00:01:19,944 --> 00:01:22,645
I should've yanked all her hair out
while I had the chance.

27
00:01:22,645 --> 00:01:24,397
I swear, I almost...

28
00:01:28,534 --> 00:01:31,597
So Kang Yeon Ja did this to your hair?

29
00:01:31,802 --> 00:01:32,802
I'm just going to...

30
00:01:33,357 --> 00:01:35,379
No, it wasn't Kang Yeon Ja.

31
00:01:35,379 --> 00:01:37,963
It was that old lady
she always hangs around with.

32
00:01:38,781 --> 00:01:40,811
I've put in so much effort
every single day...

33
00:01:41,172 --> 00:01:43,573
to protect this beautiful hair of mine.
It hurts.

34
00:01:44,294 --> 00:01:45,968
It must've hurt so much.

35
00:01:45,968 --> 00:01:47,539
How did your hair get like this?

36
00:01:48,019 --> 00:01:50,931
All right.
I'll give you a premium scalp massage.

37
00:01:50,931 --> 00:01:51,931
Hold still.

38
00:01:52,041 --> 00:01:53,515
How did your hair end up like this?

39
00:01:54,407 --> 00:01:55,573
It hurts!

40
00:01:55,573 --> 00:01:57,232
Be gentle.

41
00:01:57,729 --> 00:02:01,136
Even so, I managed to protect this. Look.

42
00:02:02,934 --> 00:02:04,259
Seriously, you practically...

43
00:02:04,726 --> 00:02:07,726
put your life on the line...

44
00:02:08,226 --> 00:02:09,821
just to get Mother's DNA test done.

45
00:02:10,438 --> 00:02:12,515
You're a true patriot.

46
00:02:13,325 --> 00:02:16,315
A patriot? What am I, some kind of parrot?

47
00:02:17,877 --> 00:02:20,508
No, a person who sacrifices themselves
to save the country...

48
00:02:20,508 --> 00:02:23,074
- So it's a good thing, right?
- Of course.

49
00:02:26,575 --> 00:02:29,819
Once the DNA test is done,

50
00:02:30,576 --> 00:02:32,864
we'll know for sure
whether she's Mother's daughter.

51
00:02:33,016 --> 00:02:33,918
Hurry up, honey.

52
00:02:33,918 --> 00:02:36,803
Okay. I'll submit it for testing today.

53
00:02:40,371 --> 00:02:43,410
I bet it's a 99.9 percent match.

54
00:02:43,410 --> 00:02:45,477
No, a mismatch.

55
00:02:47,057 --> 00:02:48,057
Mr. Cho.

56
00:02:51,886 --> 00:02:53,885
What now? What's going on this time?

57
00:02:56,627 --> 00:02:58,527
It's time for the executive meeting, sir.

58
00:02:59,267 --> 00:03:01,461
The executive meeting?

59
00:03:01,915 --> 00:03:04,795
Yes. You reviewed the report...

60
00:03:05,245 --> 00:03:06,679
submitted this morning, didn't you?

61
00:03:07,071 --> 00:03:10,459
Of course I did. I've gone through it all.

62
00:03:11,142 --> 00:03:14,542
Okay. I'll be waiting outside.

63
00:03:14,942 --> 00:03:16,642
- Okay.
- Okay.

64
00:03:20,721 --> 00:03:21,721
He didn't see this, did he?

65
00:03:22,289 --> 00:03:24,035
Even if he did, would he know what it is?

66
00:03:24,789 --> 00:03:27,875
- He really scared me.
- What did she do to your hair?

67
00:03:29,729 --> 00:03:30,963
It's already time to leave.

68
00:03:32,159 --> 00:03:33,626
Let's wrap up today's meeting here.

69
00:03:33,832 --> 00:03:34,947
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

70
00:03:34,947 --> 00:03:35,947
All right.

71
00:03:44,039 --> 00:03:45,472
This? So you saw it.

72
00:03:45,859 --> 00:03:47,959
Standing by around the clock
until you say yes.

73
00:03:48,791 --> 00:03:51,736
Carrying the ring box in my pocket all day
was harder than I thought.

74
00:03:53,249 --> 00:03:54,995
Chief, please.

75
00:03:56,145 --> 00:03:57,288
I should get going.

76
00:04:05,482 --> 00:04:08,571
What?
Now you're even wearing matching shirts?

77
00:04:09,129 --> 00:04:10,296
It's not like that.

78
00:04:11,478 --> 00:04:13,909
Of course it is. They're a lion
and a rabbit, just like you two.

79
00:04:14,497 --> 00:04:17,133
No, really.
Don't get the wrong idea, Chief.

80
00:04:17,506 --> 00:04:21,165
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, why don't you two just
go public with your relationship already?

81
00:04:21,629 --> 00:04:23,984
- Sorry?
- Help me out here.

82
00:04:25,794 --> 00:04:26,794
You don't get what I'm saying?

83
00:04:27,895 --> 00:04:29,893
I understand what you mean,

84
00:04:30,101 --> 00:04:31,992
but we're really not dating.

85
00:04:32,264 --> 00:04:34,242
How can we go public
with something that isn't true?

86
00:04:34,242 --> 00:04:35,242
Seriously.

87
00:04:35,437 --> 00:04:38,880
Do you have to officially say it
for it to count as a relationship?

88
00:04:39,515 --> 00:04:42,741
Anyone would think you're a couple.

89
00:04:44,037 --> 00:04:47,192
Don't tell me you confessed to Gyeol
and got rejected.

90
00:04:47,387 --> 00:04:48,387
Sorry?

91
00:04:50,305 --> 00:04:52,325
- Yes.
- What?

92
00:04:55,771 --> 00:04:57,771
Sorry I couldn't be of any help.

93
00:05:01,719 --> 00:05:02,919
Ko Gyeol, seriously...

94
00:05:06,771 --> 00:05:09,560
I've organized the materials into sections
as you requested.

95
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:13,045
You've got a real talent
for compiling data.

96
00:05:13,045 --> 00:05:14,045
Good work.

97
00:05:14,748 --> 00:05:16,192
I'm back.

98
00:05:20,965 --> 00:05:24,435
Ms. Cho, that shirt is the same
as Team Manager Ko's...

99
00:05:25,261 --> 00:05:27,859
Well, the thing is...

100
00:05:28,091 --> 00:05:30,149
Something got on our clothes
during our business trip,

101
00:05:30,373 --> 00:05:32,349
and Team Manager Ko bought this in a hurry
as part of a buy-one-get-one deal.

102
00:05:32,512 --> 00:05:35,581
It's a team shirt. Is there a problem?

103
00:05:36,275 --> 00:05:38,861
A team shirt? Then where's mine?

104
00:05:39,808 --> 00:05:40,808
Well...

105
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:43,309
It was our first attempt.

106
00:05:43,573 --> 00:05:46,096
Next time we go on a business trip,
we'll get shirts for the whole team.

107
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:48,755
Understood.

108
00:05:49,311 --> 00:05:51,211
- I'll be heading out first, then.
- Okay.

109
00:05:52,557 --> 00:05:53,557
A team shirt?

110
00:05:56,733 --> 00:05:58,651
- See you tomorrow.
- Goodbye.

111
00:05:59,906 --> 00:06:00,906
Take care.

112
00:06:01,333 --> 00:06:02,467
Goodbye.

113
00:06:04,272 --> 00:06:05,272
Team Manager.

114
00:06:06,503 --> 00:06:08,973
Do you have a minute?
There's something I'd like to discuss.

115
00:06:09,451 --> 00:06:12,029
Right now? Sure.

116
00:06:12,869 --> 00:06:14,751
Wait a second. Let's leave together.

117
00:06:14,751 --> 00:06:17,672
What? I can go ahead.

118
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:20,077
Are you going to keep bailing on me?

119
00:06:21,032 --> 00:06:22,032
Let's go to the meeting room.

120
00:06:28,815 --> 00:06:30,715
Yesterday was quite a shock, wasn't it?

121
00:06:31,921 --> 00:06:33,121
Well, yeah.

122
00:06:33,991 --> 00:06:37,672
I never expected Min Ho
to make a public proposal like that.

123
00:06:38,411 --> 00:06:39,411
Are you okay?

124
00:06:39,411 --> 00:06:41,432
What can I do? It already happened.

125
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:44,517
I still don't understand
what he was thinking.

126
00:06:45,543 --> 00:06:47,739
He wasn't considerate
of your feelings at all,

127
00:06:48,362 --> 00:06:52,062
but it also made me realize
just how desperate he was.

128
00:06:52,871 --> 00:06:53,871
Gyeol.

129
00:06:55,075 --> 00:06:56,075
Seung Ri.

130
00:06:57,169 --> 00:07:00,144
Do you really have no intention
of accepting Min Ho's feelings?

131
00:07:01,847 --> 00:07:03,613
How could I?

132
00:07:06,110 --> 00:07:09,461
I've told you before.
I sincerely want you to be happy.

133
00:07:10,656 --> 00:07:12,379
Min Ho may be clumsy in a lot of ways,

134
00:07:12,993 --> 00:07:14,659
but you know better than anyone...

135
00:07:15,237 --> 00:07:18,296
how much he treasures you
and how special you are to him.

136
00:07:18,296 --> 00:07:20,589
If you're telling me to accept Min Ho
because of how he feels about me,

137
00:07:20,989 --> 00:07:22,803
then why won't you accept my feelings?

138
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:24,567
We've already talked about that.

139
00:07:26,033 --> 00:07:29,167
If you're done, I'm leaving.
Someone's waiting for me.

140
00:07:29,905 --> 00:07:30,905
Someone's waiting for you?

141
00:07:32,235 --> 00:07:36,579
Fine. I know I can't do anything
about how you feel right now.

142
00:07:37,717 --> 00:07:40,183
But you don't know how it'll end.

143
00:07:40,836 --> 00:07:42,502
You don't know who'll be
the one left by your side in the end.

144
00:07:43,714 --> 00:07:46,614
That's true. No one knows the ending...

145
00:07:47,429 --> 00:07:48,529
until they've lived it.

146
00:07:50,345 --> 00:07:53,368
Let's make choices we won't regret.

147
00:07:59,534 --> 00:08:00,534
It's okay.

148
00:08:01,611 --> 00:08:03,928
He rejected Ms. Cho Eun Ae too.

149
00:08:04,436 --> 00:08:05,702
So I'm back at square one.

150
00:08:06,665 --> 00:08:08,199
I'm going to follow him.

151
00:08:09,024 --> 00:08:11,859
And in the end,
I'll be the one who stays by his side.

152
00:08:14,021 --> 00:08:17,666
What? Your hair? Why?

153
00:08:17,987 --> 00:08:20,043
If I knew, I wouldn't be so frustrated.

154
00:08:20,043 --> 00:08:23,166
I was about to give her
a piece of my mind,

155
00:08:23,539 --> 00:08:25,241
but Sun Bun ended up ripping out
a fistful of her hair,

156
00:08:25,241 --> 00:08:27,011
and she ran off.

157
00:08:27,443 --> 00:08:29,427
So I never even got the chance
to confront her.

158
00:08:29,582 --> 00:08:30,882
Good grief.

159
00:08:33,091 --> 00:08:36,539
I bet it's a 99.9 percent match.

160
00:08:36,539 --> 00:08:38,365
No, a mismatch.

161
00:08:40,215 --> 00:08:41,215
Mr. Cho.

162
00:08:45,069 --> 00:08:46,969
What now? What's going on this time?

163
00:08:48,843 --> 00:08:51,210
Just thinking about that woman...

164
00:08:51,210 --> 00:08:53,987
makes me want to tell you
to quit that job right now.

165
00:08:55,097 --> 00:08:57,432
It's not fear. It's disgust.

166
00:08:58,808 --> 00:09:00,426
Why on earth did she do that?

167
00:09:00,426 --> 00:09:03,260
I can't exactly ask CEO Ko about it.

168
00:09:03,699 --> 00:09:04,931
Don't do anything, honey.

169
00:09:05,237 --> 00:09:08,125
I'll look for the right moment
and deal with her properly.

170
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:10,563
So what if she's the CEO's wife?

171
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:14,536
Anyway, you're not hurt anywhere, right?

172
00:09:14,797 --> 00:09:17,840
Yes. Other than losing some hair.

173
00:09:19,355 --> 00:09:22,787
Last time, she came to our house,
said nothing, and stormed right out.

174
00:09:24,048 --> 00:09:27,112
I'm sorry you had to go through all that
because of me.

175
00:09:27,706 --> 00:09:29,637
Why is that your fault?

176
00:09:31,655 --> 00:09:32,655
Where's Bit Na?

177
00:09:33,265 --> 00:09:34,265
With Cho Rong.

178
00:09:35,168 --> 00:09:38,475
Since the shop's closed today,
Cho Rong's been keeping her entertained.

179
00:09:38,914 --> 00:09:39,914
I should go pick her up.

180
00:09:49,260 --> 00:09:50,365
Father, are you heading out?

181
00:09:51,179 --> 00:09:52,840
Yes.
Your mother and I are going on a date.

182
00:09:53,189 --> 00:09:54,149
We'll be home late.

183
00:09:55,660 --> 00:09:56,939
A date? Nice.

184
00:09:57,286 --> 00:09:59,077
Since it's a special date,

185
00:09:59,476 --> 00:10:01,942
stay out as long as you want.

186
00:10:02,842 --> 00:10:06,797
Yes, don't worry about the house at all.
Just go enjoy yourselves.

187
00:10:09,578 --> 00:10:10,901
The car is ready, Chairman.

188
00:10:12,877 --> 00:10:15,492
Looks like your freckles
aren't showing today.

189
00:10:15,492 --> 00:10:18,400
What? I completely forgot.

190
00:10:19,290 --> 00:10:21,648
Make sure you lock your room, Chairman.

191
00:10:22,153 --> 00:10:26,153
No. Even if a thief got into my room,
there's nothing worth stealing.

192
00:10:27,286 --> 00:10:28,286
Here, let me take that.

193
00:10:28,803 --> 00:10:31,123
- Have a good time.
- Have a good time.

194
00:10:31,123 --> 00:10:32,451
- We'll be off.
- Yes.

195
00:10:34,151 --> 00:10:35,811
A thief?

196
00:10:36,344 --> 00:10:37,930
Was he talking about us?

197
00:10:37,930 --> 00:10:39,411
Is that really what matters right now?

198
00:10:39,704 --> 00:10:41,080
The housekeeper's on vacation too.

199
00:10:41,339 --> 00:10:43,939
Today,
it's just the two of us in this house.

200
00:10:44,283 --> 00:10:45,825
Do you realize
what an opportunity this is?

201
00:10:45,825 --> 00:10:48,427
Exactly. It's not every day
we get a chance like this.

202
00:10:49,631 --> 00:10:50,731
Wait.

203
00:10:50,732 --> 00:10:51,766
What now?

204
00:10:51,958 --> 00:10:54,627
The mission we're carrying out today...

205
00:10:54,889 --> 00:10:57,589
is on a completely different level
from an ordinary safecracking job.

206
00:10:59,048 --> 00:11:02,808
We're securing the will containing
Kangsu Group's future blueprint,

207
00:11:02,808 --> 00:11:04,568
and at the same time...

208
00:11:04,568 --> 00:11:07,434
And proving whether Kang Yeon Ja
is that child or not?

209
00:11:07,853 --> 00:11:09,605
So what? Hurry.

210
00:11:22,893 --> 00:11:24,419
Wait.

211
00:11:29,893 --> 00:11:32,250
Crystal, am I shaking right now?

212
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:34,150
What are you doing?
Want me to press it for you?

213
00:11:34,150 --> 00:11:35,320
No.

214
00:11:36,672 --> 00:11:38,987
I can't leave something this dirty to you.

215
00:11:39,209 --> 00:11:41,943
I'll do all the dirty work myself. Wait.

216
00:11:45,164 --> 00:11:48,130
Please enter the password or fingerprint.

217
00:11:52,793 --> 00:11:54,493
Unregistered number.

218
00:11:55,957 --> 00:11:57,005
What happened?

219
00:11:57,449 --> 00:11:59,792
Didn't you say Kang Yeon Ja's birthday
was February 4th?

220
00:12:00,283 --> 00:12:02,705
That's definitely right.
Maybe I entered it wrong.

221
00:12:02,705 --> 00:12:04,271
- Again.
- Okay.

222
00:12:05,283 --> 00:12:06,283
Password.

223
00:12:10,304 --> 00:12:12,289
- Unregistered number.
- That's not it.

224
00:12:12,289 --> 00:12:13,289
No?

225
00:12:14,283 --> 00:12:16,808
Wait, isn't this even better?

226
00:12:17,299 --> 00:12:19,725
It means Kang Yeon Ja
isn't Mother's daughter.

227
00:12:22,224 --> 00:12:23,600
Sure, but then...

228
00:12:24,009 --> 00:12:25,707
what about that necklace?

229
00:12:25,927 --> 00:12:28,725
Right. Did she pick it up somewhere?

230
00:12:29,166 --> 00:12:30,632
You said the woman in the photo
was Mother too.

231
00:12:30,632 --> 00:12:33,741
Well, the photo's really old,

232
00:12:34,063 --> 00:12:35,880
and my eyesight isn't what it used to be.

233
00:12:37,025 --> 00:12:39,803
Hold on. This actually worked out great.

234
00:12:41,249 --> 00:12:43,249
Most importantly, I saved my nose.
My precious nose.

235
00:12:43,249 --> 00:12:44,315
Wait.

236
00:12:46,019 --> 00:12:48,587
- Retreat.
- Retreat.

237
00:12:51,422 --> 00:12:52,722
You don't have to do that now.

238
00:12:53,805 --> 00:12:54,805
Really?

239
00:12:55,313 --> 00:12:56,313
Seriously.

240
00:12:58,436 --> 00:13:01,115
Son, how many days has it been
since we've seen you?

241
00:13:01,557 --> 00:13:02,557
I'm sorry.

242
00:13:02,842 --> 00:13:04,603
I've been coming home at dawn
and leaving early in the morning.

243
00:13:05,173 --> 00:13:06,344
What's with that outfit?

244
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:08,395
Are Grandma and Grandpa not home?

245
00:13:08,395 --> 00:13:10,213
Looks like they went on a date.

246
00:13:10,499 --> 00:13:12,599
I think Gyeol's spending the whole day
with them.

247
00:13:13,064 --> 00:13:14,064
Gyeol is?

248
00:13:14,064 --> 00:13:16,445
You little punk, come sit down.

249
00:13:16,954 --> 00:13:17,988
You too.

250
00:13:17,988 --> 00:13:19,854
Right, we have something
to discuss with you, Min Ho.

251
00:13:21,930 --> 00:13:24,632
I need to stop by the office
and then go to Mr. Seo's house.

252
00:13:25,102 --> 00:13:26,102
Let's talk later.

253
00:13:26,214 --> 00:13:29,243
What? Mr. Seo's house?
Are you really going to keep this up?

254
00:13:29,577 --> 00:13:31,440
You embarrassed me
in front of the entire company.

255
00:13:31,851 --> 00:13:32,951
Have you learned nothing?

256
00:13:32,951 --> 00:13:35,351
Ko Min Ho, aren't you being too much?

257
00:13:35,761 --> 00:13:39,184
You don't care one bit about how we feel.
All you think about is Seung Ri.

258
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:40,919
I'm heading out.

259
00:13:41,813 --> 00:13:42,813
Stop right there!

260
00:13:43,518 --> 00:13:44,916
If you keep this up...

261
00:13:44,916 --> 00:13:45,982
I already told you.

262
00:13:46,419 --> 00:13:49,032
If you oppose Seung Ri and me,
I'll quit everything.

263
00:13:49,657 --> 00:13:50,907
I wasn't joking.

264
00:13:52,949 --> 00:13:55,872
You punk!
How dare you threaten your parents?

265
00:13:57,179 --> 00:13:58,712
What do we do?

266
00:13:58,712 --> 00:14:00,861
Are we really going to lose him to her?

267
00:14:02,696 --> 00:14:05,184
I've wanted to meet you for a long time.

268
00:14:05,415 --> 00:14:06,815
And now, we're finally meeting.

269
00:14:08,141 --> 00:14:09,641
It's an honor, Chairman.

270
00:14:11,349 --> 00:14:15,136
I was thrilled when I heard
the developer who created an AI...

271
00:14:15,781 --> 00:14:19,637
so useful for seniors
had joined the same team as our Gyeol.

272
00:14:19,956 --> 00:14:24,712
And now, you're even living together.
I've been so curious.

273
00:14:26,015 --> 00:14:27,981
She really does resemble her mother,
doesn't she?

274
00:14:29,728 --> 00:14:31,712
Now that I look closely, she does.

275
00:14:32,210 --> 00:14:36,173
I knew there was something familiar
about her face.

276
00:14:40,205 --> 00:14:42,529
If you request a song here,
they'll play it for you.

277
00:14:42,529 --> 00:14:43,929
Is there anything you'd like to hear?

278
00:14:44,382 --> 00:14:47,403
Nothing comes to mind right away.

279
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:50,512
How about "Wild Rose?"

280
00:14:50,910 --> 00:14:52,565
It's one
of Ms. Cho Eun Ae's favorite songs.

281
00:14:52,969 --> 00:14:55,725
Apparently, her mother used to sing it
as a lullaby.

282
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:59,305
Really? Then let's request that one.

283
00:14:59,305 --> 00:15:00,471
Okay.

284
00:15:16,752 --> 00:15:22,227
<i>On the way to Mom's work</i>

285
00:15:22,987 --> 00:15:26,336
<i>White wild rose</i>

286
00:15:28,073 --> 00:15:33,573
<i>The white petals of the wild rose</i>

287
00:15:34,075 --> 00:15:37,675
<i>Taste good too</i>

288
00:15:39,470 --> 00:15:45,003
<i>On hungry days</i>

289
00:15:45,566 --> 00:15:49,795
<i>I quietly picked and ate them</i>

290
00:15:51,197 --> 00:15:56,497
<i>Calling "Mom, Mom"</i>

291
00:15:56,995 --> 00:15:59,339
<i>I ate them</i>

292
00:15:59,339 --> 00:16:00,339
Today you're checking out...

293
00:16:00,741 --> 00:16:03,579
places to include in Joy's program, right?

294
00:16:03,579 --> 00:16:07,136
Yes.
We're updating the senior dating course,

295
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,349
and we'd love to hear your thoughts...

296
00:16:09,349 --> 00:16:11,741
after experiencing it yourselves.

297
00:16:13,069 --> 00:16:16,701
Really? I'm looking forward to it.

298
00:16:23,668 --> 00:16:24,934
(Deoki Snack Bar, Steamed Buns)

299
00:16:39,168 --> 00:16:41,700
Grandpa and Grandma,
you look great in those.

300
00:16:41,700 --> 00:16:43,272
Come on.

301
00:16:43,272 --> 00:16:47,005
With these wrinkled old faces?
How embarrassing.

302
00:16:47,005 --> 00:16:49,560
Not at all. You look wonderful.

303
00:16:50,085 --> 00:16:51,416
That's exactly what I mean.

304
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:55,081
Yeong Hwa still looks like
an innocent high school girl.

305
00:16:55,081 --> 00:16:58,047
Stop teasing me. People will hear you.

306
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,480
Grandpa, this hat...

307
00:17:00,736 --> 00:17:03,197
looks much better on you like this.

308
00:17:03,367 --> 00:17:07,197
Really?
Then I need to tuck this bag under my arm.

309
00:17:07,427 --> 00:17:08,776
This is the proper look.

310
00:17:09,858 --> 00:17:12,069
Grandpa, you know what you're doing.

311
00:17:12,958 --> 00:17:13,958
Come over here, both of you.

312
00:17:13,958 --> 00:17:16,993
(New Student Uniform Bag Shop)

313
00:17:16,993 --> 00:17:17,993
Have a seat here.

314
00:17:18,898 --> 00:17:20,221
I'll take your picture.

315
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,917
Okay, here we go.

316
00:17:24,351 --> 00:17:25,451
One, two, three.

317
00:17:26,159 --> 00:17:29,159
Grandpa, put your arm around Grandma.

318
00:17:33,679 --> 00:17:35,123
Perfect. Got it.

319
00:17:36,306 --> 00:17:37,970
Now you two sit down.

320
00:17:37,970 --> 00:17:39,357
I will take your picture.

321
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:41,226
What? Us?

322
00:17:41,688 --> 00:17:42,754
Go on.

323
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:45,520
Okay.

324
00:17:45,693 --> 00:17:46,693
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

325
00:17:49,062 --> 00:17:50,304
All right, I'm taking it.

326
00:17:51,051 --> 00:17:52,751
You two should sit a little closer.

327
00:17:52,751 --> 00:17:54,013
You're way too far apart.

328
00:17:55,663 --> 00:17:57,605
Closer.

329
00:17:58,695 --> 00:17:59,695
Okay.

330
00:18:00,173 --> 00:18:02,224
Even closer. More.

331
00:18:02,984 --> 00:18:03,984
- Okay.
- That's it.

332
00:18:05,523 --> 00:18:07,123
Link arms too, Eun Ae.

333
00:18:07,123 --> 00:18:08,771
Sorry? Link arms?

334
00:18:08,771 --> 00:18:10,709
Yes. Link arms.

335
00:18:11,405 --> 00:18:12,405
Come on, do it.

336
00:18:14,821 --> 00:18:16,096
Hurry up.

337
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:22,501
That's it. One, two.

338
00:18:23,093 --> 00:18:25,043
Got it. Let's take another.

339
00:18:25,752 --> 00:18:27,531
Smile. Give me a smile.

340
00:18:29,601 --> 00:18:32,544
Okay, here we go. Peekaboo!

341
00:18:37,057 --> 00:18:39,072
- Look at this jar.
- Okay.

342
00:18:39,546 --> 00:18:41,246
There's a metal cage too.

343
00:18:42,203 --> 00:18:44,504
I haven't seen a mailbox in ages.

344
00:18:44,504 --> 00:18:46,363
- Shaved ice.
- It is shaved ice.

345
00:18:46,363 --> 00:18:47,617
This is an old ice cream container.

346
00:18:47,617 --> 00:18:48,617
You're right.

347
00:18:50,162 --> 00:18:51,162
Here.

348
00:19:28,693 --> 00:19:29,993
This...

349
00:19:31,022 --> 00:19:32,022
What's wrong?

350
00:19:33,079 --> 00:19:34,776
My mother has one of these too.

351
00:19:44,119 --> 00:19:45,219
- That one.
- This?

352
00:19:51,630 --> 00:19:52,630
Let me do it. Move aside.

353
00:19:54,349 --> 00:19:55,349
This one.

354
00:19:56,871 --> 00:19:57,871
This one.

355
00:20:05,361 --> 00:20:07,455
All right, let's see.

356
00:20:07,455 --> 00:20:10,489
Who's going to be the lucky one?

357
00:20:14,407 --> 00:20:16,757
I'll try one more time.

358
00:20:17,355 --> 00:20:18,939
Look at the lens.

359
00:20:37,501 --> 00:20:39,163
- Hello.
- Welcome.

360
00:20:39,993 --> 00:20:42,464
I brought these
because they reminded me of you, Mother.

361
00:20:42,937 --> 00:20:45,137
Goodness, thank you.

362
00:20:45,966 --> 00:20:46,966
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

363
00:20:47,205 --> 00:20:48,205
- Sit down.
- Okay.

364
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:51,037
Seung Ri left for work early this morning.

365
00:20:51,037 --> 00:20:52,037
Yes, I know.

366
00:20:52,190 --> 00:20:54,360
I stopped by the office
and saw her on my way here.

367
00:20:56,162 --> 00:20:59,104
I heard what happened.
What are you going to do?

368
00:20:59,552 --> 00:21:01,712
I feel so sorry for you, Min Ho.

369
00:21:01,712 --> 00:21:03,755
It's okay. I'm fine.

370
00:21:04,004 --> 00:21:07,370
Fine? She rejected you
in front of the whole company.

371
00:21:07,874 --> 00:21:09,931
Even I think that was too much.

372
00:21:10,149 --> 00:21:12,749
Anyway, what are you going to do?

373
00:21:13,353 --> 00:21:14,792
Seung Ri won't budge.

374
00:21:15,371 --> 00:21:18,803
If I keep knocking,
I'm sure her heart will open someday.

375
00:21:19,251 --> 00:21:21,451
I'm not giving up on Seung Ri.

376
00:21:24,686 --> 00:21:26,864
The reason I called you here today...

377
00:21:27,844 --> 00:21:28,910
is because, from this day forward,

378
00:21:29,771 --> 00:21:32,267
I consider you my son-in-law.

379
00:21:33,059 --> 00:21:34,059
Honey.

380
00:21:34,483 --> 00:21:36,221
Thank you so much, Mother.

381
00:21:36,842 --> 00:21:39,269
I vote for that too.

382
00:21:39,826 --> 00:21:43,040
Ever since I was little, I've always
pictured you as my brother-in-law.

383
00:21:44,373 --> 00:21:45,933
Thanks, brother-in-law.

384
00:21:47,093 --> 00:21:48,193
I'll be in the studio.

385
00:21:48,530 --> 00:21:49,787
Brother-in-law, you can do it!

386
00:21:50,194 --> 00:21:52,069
- I can do it!
- See you later.

387
00:21:53,371 --> 00:21:56,872
See? Seung Wu and I
are completely on your side.

388
00:21:57,707 --> 00:22:00,837
And even if Gwon Sik doesn't say it,
he's on your side too.

389
00:22:01,789 --> 00:22:03,489
We'll all stick together...

390
00:22:03,849 --> 00:22:06,112
and keep supporting you.

391
00:22:06,567 --> 00:22:08,456
Thank you so much, Mother and Father.

392
00:22:10,013 --> 00:22:11,013
Seriously.

393
00:22:40,028 --> 00:22:41,028
You're still here?

394
00:22:41,845 --> 00:22:43,701
Have you written a lot?

395
00:22:43,707 --> 00:22:44,707
That's none of your business.

396
00:22:44,981 --> 00:22:47,800
Hey now, "none of your business?"

397
00:22:48,633 --> 00:22:49,688
Maybe if we weren't in business.

398
00:22:49,688 --> 00:22:51,256
But we are, so it's "all" of my business.

399
00:22:52,880 --> 00:22:54,368
What kind of dad joke is that?

400
00:22:58,781 --> 00:22:59,815
Just a second.

401
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:03,709
You know Ban Do Yeon,
the lead of "The ER Witch?"

402
00:23:03,989 --> 00:23:07,216
The more I look at her,
the more she reminds me of you.

403
00:23:07,219 --> 00:23:08,536
I'd like to do a sketch.

404
00:23:08,536 --> 00:23:11,786
Would you be my model?

405
00:23:11,786 --> 00:23:13,549
What? A model?

406
00:23:14,152 --> 00:23:15,764
It's time for me to go home.

407
00:23:15,764 --> 00:23:16,830
Just a minute.

408
00:23:17,360 --> 00:23:19,048
It won't take long. Stay right there.

409
00:23:21,945 --> 00:23:24,720
Let's see. Okay.

410
00:23:28,132 --> 00:23:29,798
Perfect. You look so natural right now.

411
00:23:29,798 --> 00:23:30,981
This is great.

412
00:23:30,981 --> 00:23:33,376
Okay, tuck your hair once more. Okay.

413
00:23:33,643 --> 00:23:34,977
He's making me do all sorts of things.

414
00:23:40,397 --> 00:23:41,397
Wait.

415
00:23:42,611 --> 00:23:45,885
Would you mind taking off your glasses?

416
00:23:45,885 --> 00:23:48,373
What? Take off my glasses?

417
00:23:48,677 --> 00:23:52,016
I want to try drawing Ban Do Yeon
wearing contact lenses.

418
00:23:52,016 --> 00:23:55,613
Excuse me. These glasses
are basically part of my body.

419
00:23:57,415 --> 00:23:58,515
Then hurry up and draw.

420
00:24:15,170 --> 00:24:16,170
She's beautiful.

421
00:24:17,388 --> 00:24:18,411
Are you done?

422
00:24:48,446 --> 00:24:50,246
What's this?

423
00:24:50,949 --> 00:24:52,744
You said you wanted a housewarming party.

424
00:24:54,016 --> 00:24:57,240
Things have been tense lately at home,
so instead of doing it with everyone,

425
00:24:57,710 --> 00:24:59,077
I kept it simple.

426
00:25:02,783 --> 00:25:05,783
Congratulations on becoming
part of our family.

427
00:25:08,530 --> 00:25:10,363
Now blow out the candles.

428
00:25:12,408 --> 00:25:14,874
Could you say that one more time?

429
00:25:15,651 --> 00:25:16,651
What?

430
00:25:19,065 --> 00:25:22,899
Congratulations on becoming
part of our family, Team Manager.

431
00:25:26,849 --> 00:25:30,483
Thank you for accepting me as family.

432
00:25:45,467 --> 00:25:47,933
Seeing your grandma and grandpa
so happy today...

433
00:25:48,723 --> 00:25:50,089
was wonderful.

434
00:25:50,353 --> 00:25:51,653
It's all thanks to you, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

435
00:25:52,598 --> 00:25:53,598
Not at all.

436
00:25:55,413 --> 00:25:57,853
Watching them made me realize something.

437
00:25:59,533 --> 00:26:01,456
"I hope I grow old like that someday."

438
00:26:03,001 --> 00:26:05,899
Remembering each other at our brightest,

439
00:26:06,574 --> 00:26:09,908
and growing old together...

440
00:26:10,594 --> 00:26:12,828
with someone who can always
see you as the most handsome...

441
00:26:14,004 --> 00:26:15,515
or most beautiful person in the world
sounds perfect.

442
00:26:21,310 --> 00:26:22,840
Why are you looking at me like that?

443
00:26:24,143 --> 00:26:27,577
Even when you're a gray-haired,
wrinkled grandma,

444
00:26:29,759 --> 00:26:31,059
you'll still be beautiful.

445
00:26:31,809 --> 00:26:32,809
What?

446
00:26:34,984 --> 00:26:38,787
Well, even when you're a grandpa,

447
00:26:40,454 --> 00:26:41,854
you'll still be handsome too.

448
00:26:43,551 --> 00:26:44,751
The most handsome in the world.

449
00:26:53,115 --> 00:26:54,424
Shall we go?

450
00:27:03,773 --> 00:27:04,773
Team Manager.

451
00:27:06,209 --> 00:27:09,832
I don't think I can do this anymore.

452
00:27:12,538 --> 00:27:14,038
No matter how hard I try to stop it...

453
00:27:15,856 --> 00:27:17,256
No matter how hard I try
to hold it back...

454
00:27:23,735 --> 00:27:26,669
I don't think I can anymore.

455
00:28:21,597 --> 00:28:23,163
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
